  "name": "debitTransaction",
  "domain": "MultiDebitTransaction",
  "operationType": "CREATE",
  "invocationType": [
    "SYNC"
  ],
  "description": [
    "This service orchestrates a multi-debit (and broader multi-leg) transaction creation flow, supporting feature types such as FundTransfer, MultiCreditTransaction, MultiDebitTransaction, OpenAccount, AccountClosure, and TDAccountPreClosure. It begins by validating the incoming request using rules-engine-driven checks tailored to the detected feature type, throwing structured validation exceptions for any field-level failures. Once validated, the service fetches the relevant deposit account records and retrieves the associated customer and account contracts, enriching each transaction leg with contract details and throwing an exception if contract data is missing or invalid. It then verifies that debit operations are permitted on the applicable accounts, evaluates multi-leg transaction limits (storing external reference IDs for potential reversal), and determines whether fees apply to any legs based on the contract configuration. The service prepares the transaction payload and process-context state \u2014 including fee-aware state transitions \u2014 before delegating execution to an external transaction system; if that call fails and limit reversal is enabled, it reverses any consumed operational limits before re-throwing the error. On success, it persists account, document, and notice entities to the database, extracts the transaction result from the process context, and returns a 201 Created response to the caller."
  ],
